# React Component Patterns

## 1. File Naming (kebab-case)

Component files use **kebab-case**, not PascalCase. PascalCase is only for component names inside the file.

```
✅ GOOD
components/animated-splash/animated-splash.tsx
components/user-profile/user-profile.tsx

❌ BAD
components/AnimatedSplash.tsx
components/UserProfile.tsx
```

## 2. Named Exports (no default)

Always use named exports, never `export default`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
export default function AnimatedSplash() { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
export const AnimatedSplash = () => { ... }
```

## 3. Arrow Functions for Components

Components must be arrow functions, not regular functions.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
function AnimatedSplash() {
  return <View>...</View>;
}

// ✅ GOOD
const AnimatedSplash = () => {
  return <View>...</View>;
};
```

## 4. Styles in Separate Files

Styles live in a dedicated file next to the component, not inline in the component file.

```
✅ GOOD
components/animated-splash/
  animated-splash.tsx   ← component logic only
  styles.ts            ← styles
  constants.ts

// animated-splash.tsx
import { styles } from './styles';
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - styles inside component file
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { flex: 1 },
});
```
